present the medians?

3
00:00:09,980 --> 00:00:12,690
Well you'll see if you read a lot of the
medical literature,

4
00:00:12,690 --> 00:00:14,260
that most people go with the means.

5
00:00:14,260 --> 00:00:17,530
I think most people feel very comfortable
with the means.

6
00:00:17,530 --> 00:00:19,530
That's what they're typically used to
seeing.

7
00:00:19,530 --> 00:00:22,110
So a lot of authors will present means.

8
00:00:22,110 --> 00:00:24,960
It turns out, however, there are cases, a
lot of cases, actually,

9
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:27,745
where it would be better to report the
median.

10
00:00:27,745 --> 00:00:31,550
Because if you have skewed data, if you
have extreme values,

11
00:00:31,550 --> 00:00:36,690
as we've seen, those extreme values can
influence, can affect the mean,

12
00:00:36,690 --> 00:00:39,590
and so the mean might be misleading.

13
00:00:39,590 --> 00:00:42,900
Where as the median doesn't get affected
by those extreme values.

14
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:45,770
So the median might be a better
representation in that case of

15
00:00:45,770 --> 00:00:47,630
the center of the data.

16
00:00:47,630 --> 00:00:49,730
So let me just illustrate that.

